REQUEST (Node ServerRequest)

request.method
request.url
request.headers
request.body
request.httpVersion

RESPONSE (Node ServerResponse)

response.status
response.headers
response.body
respones.contentLength
respones.contentType

MESSAGE (Object)

message.headers
message.input
message.input.url
message.input.path
message.input.body
message.output
message.output.body
message.status
message.__request
message.__response

MESSAGE HANDLER (Function)

A message handler (or simply handler) takes a request message (and an optional handler to intercept) and returns a future of a response message.

function handleSomething(request) {
  var response = {output: {body: ''}, status: 200};
  return response;
};

function interceptNextHandler(request, nextHandler) {
  return nextHandler(request);
};
